<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[96,730,1542,1693]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
This close relative of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otto &amp; Hill" authorityYear="2011" box="[373,488,1542,1567]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harrisi">
<emphasis box="[373,488,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. harrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the southern coastal region of Australia has a slightly different pattern of white stripes across the fan. Unlike 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otto &amp; Hill" authorityYear="2011" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harrisi">
<emphasis box="[701,728,1605,1630]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[96,170,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">harrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Otto &amp; Hill" authorityYear="2016" box="[256,377,1636,1661]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Maratus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobatus">
<emphasis box="[256,377,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. lobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not raise legs III as they display their elevated and expanded fan to females.
</paragraph>
